FFA members learn by doing. Junior FFA members Karleigh Schoenberger and Clay Brillhart have spent time at home over the past two months caring for their livestock projects.

FFA members conduct Supervised Agricultural Experiences where one option is to own and operate your own livestock production operation like Clay and Karleigh.

April 1 was Census Day, but it’s not too late to complete the 2020 Census! Your response to the 2020 Census matters, and the results can shape many different aspects of your community over the next decade.
This needs to be remedied to make certain none of our communities are at a disadvantage over the next decade due to an incomplete count. Click here to fill out the Census now. https://my2020census.gov/

post_text:
The Uniontown High School/Junior High yearbook is now on sale! The school yearbook is part of the tradition and experience of being a high school or junior high school student. It is a reminder of friendships, challenges, and the adventures a child experiences in the process of learning, to which you also contributed. Don't miss having it among your special mementos.

Yearbooks are only $40 and can be purchased online with a credit card or a debit card at www.yearbookforever.com. You can also order your copy by mailing a check to the school in the care of the high school office.

Don't be left without yours. The deadline to order your copy is April 30th. This is a much earlier date than in years past.

post_text:
We kicked off chapter officer interviews today like we never have before!! I conducted 4 interview sessions with 4 of our 10 candidates this afternoon via Zoom! Each candidate was asked a series of questions and recorded. Tomorrow the other 6 candidates will be asked the same questions and of course will be recorded.

Once all 10 have been interviewed, they will also record a short speech, upload to Youtube and share the link with me. At that point their interviews, speeches and applications will be shared with the interview judging panel for evaluation.

FFA members are making the best of this situation and making things happen!

Shoutout to senior Colt Eck and sophomore Bryce Eck on completing the fabrication of this big square bale feeder on their own during this past week!! He already has an order for 3 more!! If anyone is interested in purchasing one, let me know and I can get you in touch with the boys.

Even though the school year isn’t finishing up like we all hoped, there are some cool things that will happen over the next several weeks. This is an example of that!

I’m also excited to report that Mr. Reith is all in on students doing projects that relate to their elective courses and receiving class grades for it. I will have more information on what that looks like as we begin meeting over Zoom!

I’m also excited to report that Mr. Reith is all in on students doing projects that relate to their elective courses and receiving class grades for it. I will have more information on what that looks like as we begin meeting over Zoom!

post_text:
The FFA Trip is still happening!

Despite the Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo cancelling due to the Coronavirus scare, we are still leaving tomorrow morning at 4:00 AM.

We will continue with our tours tomorrow and our trip to Six Flags on Friday. Saturday we will attend the Oklahoma Youth Expo Livestock Show in Oklahoma City instead of going on to Houston.

We will still return home on Sunday afternoon, maybe a little earlier than originally planned.

post_text: Congratulations to the Uniontown Eagles HS Basketball teams on a clean sweep tonight against Northeast. Both the Boys and Girls JV teams won. post_text:
We will begin our yearly dental screenings on Monday, February 24th. Hygienist from Community Health Center of SEK will provide these services on Monday and Tuesday to any student in the district who signed consent. This free service provides screening, fluoride application, cleaning and sealants. If you have questions or comments, please contact us at 620-756-4335.

Thank you to CHC of SEK!

post_text: WBE has an open Kindergarten position for the 2020-21 school year. Any interested parties could find the application at https://www.uniontown235.org/o/uniontown-usd-235/browse/54541. We are a dynamic building with a strong instructional legacy. Please share with those that can help us continue to be a leader in our field. Completed applications can be mailed to WBE or emailed to Mr. Eden at veden@uniontown235.org.

post_text:
Thanks for all the support with the Move to Give fundraiser!! We are excited to see the jars filling up! The last day to bring money will be on Friday (February 21st) for a chance to win a pizza party! Proceeds will go towards updating the playground. Below are the current rankings and totals for the competition.

1st Place: Kindergarten with $64.60
2nd Place: First Grade with $44.92
3rd Place: Third Grade with $28.74
4th Place: Second Grade with $26.86
5th Place: PreK with $17.52
6th Place: Fifth Grade with $13.36
7th Place: Sixth Grade with $13.27
8th Place: Fourth Grade with $6.17
